{
  "text": "The CPSO model consists of four algorithms, from now on, our study specifically focused on CPSO-HK algorithm which covers the other three ones. Fig. 2 shows the structure of CPSO-HK algorithm. \"When to switch between CPSO-SK and PSO?\" is a question proposed by Van den Bergh in [CITATION_1] . For designing such a robust, general and adaptive mechanism consider the following scenarios in CPSO-HK algorithm: Reviewing the discussed scenarios, interleave execution of CPSO-SK and PSO seems to be a naIve form of cooperation between these two algorithms. A proper choice is to form an adaptive cooperation between CPSO-SK and PSO algorithms.",
  "citation_candidates": [
